String reversal
Anagram check
Pattern matching (Naive)
KMP Algorithm (advanced)
Rabin-Karp
🔥 7. Linked List Algorithms
Reverse Linked List
Detect cycle (Floyd’s Algorithm)
Merge two lists
Find middle element
🔥 8. Stack & Queue Algorithms
Valid Parentheses
Next Greater Element
LRU Cache
Min Stack
🔥 9. Tree Algorithms
Tree Traversals:
Inorder
Preorder
Postorder
Level Order Traversal
Height of tree
Lowest Common Ancestor
🔥 10. Graph Algorithms (Very Important for Top Companies)
BFS (Breadth First Search)
DFS (Depth First Search)
Dijkstra’s Algorithm
Bellman-Ford
Floyd-Warshall
Topological Sort
Kruskal’s Algorithm
Prim’s Algorithm
🔥 11. Dynamic Programming (Most Powerful)
Fibonacci (DP)
Knapsack Problem
Longest Common Subsequence (LCS)
Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS)
Matrix Chain Multiplication
🔥 12. Greedy Algorithms
Activity Selection
Fractional Knapsack
Huffman Coding
🔥 13. Bit Manipulation
Check even/odd
Power of 2
XOR tricks
Swap without temp
🔥 14. Advanced (For High-Level Interviews)
Segment Tree
Fenwick Tree (Binary Indexed Tree)
Trie
Disjoint Set (Union-Find)
💡 Important Truth (Listen Carefully)

You don’t need “all algorithms.”

👉 You need:

Strong basics
Practice + pattern recognition
Consistency
🚀 Best Roadmap for YOU (Based on your level)

Since you are learning Java + preparing for interviews:

Week Plan:
Week 1–2 → Basics + Arrays
Week 3 → Sorting + Searching
Week 4 → Recursion
Week 5 → Linked List + Stack
Week 6 → Trees
